{"type":"message","id":"74bf7363","parentId":"8a157be4","timestamp":"2026-02-15T11:00:28.669Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Considering Project Setup**\n\nI've taken a quick glance at the project files. I've noted the `requirements.txt` and `pyproject.toml` files, which gives me an immediate sense of the Python environment. I'll need to dig into `pyproject.toml` to determine if Poetry is in use, as that influences dependency management.\n\n\n**Constructing System Documentation**\n\nI'm currently focused on the documentation, specifically the `SYSTEM_FLOW.md` file. I'm building out the Mermaid diagram based on the file structure, outlining interactions between components like the Telegram Update handler, Command Center, and Trading Automation. I'll include details about LangFuse, OpenTelemetry, and Streamlit integration. The next step is to initiate `docs_archive` folder and create the `SYSTEM_FLOW.md` file.\n\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"exec_1771153228660_340","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"mkdir -p D:\\Dmarket_bot\\docs_archive"},"thoughtSignature":""}],"api":"google-vertex","provider":"google-vertex","model":"gemini-3-pro-preview","usage":{"input":27615,"output":392,"cacheRead":25565,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":28007,"cost":{"input":0.055229999999999994,"output":0.004704,"cacheRead":0.005113,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.065047}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1771153221497}}
