{"type":"message","id":"13897c65","parentId":"5fcde329","timestamp":"2026-02-15T11:00:49.316Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"exec_1771153248220_342","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"usage: pyreverse [options]\r\n\r\nCreate UML diagrams for classes and modules in <packages>.\r\n\r\noptions:\r\n  -h, --help            show this help message and exit\r\n\r\nPyreverse:\r\n  Base class providing common behaviour for pyreverse commands.\r\n\r\n  --filter-mode <mode>, -f <mode>\r\n                        filter attributes and functions according to <mode>.\r\n                        Correct modes are : 'PUB_ONLY' filter all non public\r\n                        attributes [DEFAULT], equivalent to PRIVATE+SPECIAL_A\r\n                        'ALL' no filter 'SPECIAL' filter Python special\r\n                        functions except constructor 'OTHER' filter protected\r\n                        and private attributes (default: PUB_ONLY)\r\n  --class <class>, -c <class>\r\n                        create a class diagram with all classes related to\r\n                        <class>; this uses by default the options -ASmy\r\n                        (default: [])\r\n  --show-ancestors <ancestor>, -a <ancestor>\r\n                        show <ancestor> generations of ancestor classes not in\r\n                        <projects> (default: None)\r\n  --all-ancestors, -A   show all ancestors off all classes in <projects>\r\n                        (default: None)\r\n  --show-associated <association_level>, -s <association_level>\r\n                        show <association_level> levels of associated classes\r\n                        not in <projects> (default: None)\r\n  --all-associated, -S  show recursively all associated off all associated\r\n                        classes (default: None)\r\n  --show-builtin, -b    include builtin objects in representation of classes\r\n                        (default: False)\r\n  --module-names <y or n>, -m <y or n>\r\n                        include module name in representation of classes\r\n                        (default: None)\r\n  --only-classnames, -k\r\n                        don't show attributes and methods in the class boxes;\r\n                        this disables -f values (default: False)\r\n  --output <format>, -o <format>\r\n                        create a *.<format> output file if format is\r\n                        available. Available formats are: dot, vcg, puml,\r\n                        plantuml, mmd, html. Any other format will be tried to\r\n                        create by means of the 'dot' command line tool, which\r\n                        requires a graphviz installation. (default: dot)\r\n  --colorized           Use colored output. Classes/modules of the same\r\n                        package get the same color. (default: False)\r\n  --max-color-depth <depth>\r\n                        Use separate colors up to package depth of <depth>\r\n                        (default: 2)\r\n  --color-palette <color1,color2,...>\r\n                        Comma separated list of colors to use (default:\r\n                        ('aliceblue', 'antiquewhite', 'aquamarine',\r\n                        'burlywood', 'cadetblue', 'chartreuse', 'chocolate',\r\n                        'coral', 'cornflowerblue', 'cyan', 'darkgoldenrod',\r\n                        'darkseagreen', 'dodgerblue', 'forestgreen', 'gold',\r\n                        'hotpink', 'mediumspringgreen'))\r\n  --ignore <file[,file...]>\r\n                        Files or directories to be skipped. They should be\r\n                        base names, not paths. (default: ('CVS',))\r\n  --project <project name>, -p <project name>\r\n                        set the project name. (default: )\r\n  --output-directory <output_directory>, -d <output_directory>\r\n                        set the output directory path. (default: )\r\n  --source-roots <path>[,<path>...]\r\n                        Add paths to the list of the source roots. Supports\r\n                        globbing patterns. The source root is an absolute path\r\n                        or a path relative to the current working directory\r\n                        used to determine a package namespace for modules\r\n                        located under the source root. (default: ())"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":1086,"aggregated":"usage: pyreverse [options]\r\n\r\nCreate UML diagrams for classes and modules in <packages>.\r\n\r\noptions:\r\n  -h, --help            show this help message and exit\r\n\r\nPyreverse:\r\n  Base class providing common behaviour for pyreverse commands.\r\n\r\n  --filter-mode <mode>, -f <mode>\r\n                        filter attributes and functions according to <mode>.\r\n                        Correct modes are : 'PUB_ONLY' filter all non public\r\n                        attributes [DEFAULT], equivalent to PRIVATE+SPECIAL_A\r\n                        'ALL' no filter 'SPECIAL' filter Python special\r\n                        functions except constructor 'OTHER' filter protected\r\n                        and private attributes (default: PUB_ONLY)\r\n  --class <class>, -c <class>\r\n                        create a class diagram with all classes related to\r\n                        <class>; this uses by default the options -ASmy\r\n                        (default: [])\r\n  --show-ancestors <ancestor>, -a <ancestor>\r\n                        show <ancestor> generations of ancestor classes not in\r\n                        <projects> (default: None)\r\n  --all-ancestors, -A   show all ancestors off all classes in <projects>\r\n                        (default: None)\r\n  --show-associated <association_level>, -s <association_level>\r\n                        show <association_level> levels of associated classes\r\n                        not in <projects> (default: None)\r\n  --all-associated, -S  show recursively all associated off all associated\r\n                        classes (default: None)\r\n  --show-builtin, -b    include builtin objects in representation of classes\r\n                        (default: False)\r\n  --module-names <y or n>, -m <y or n>\r\n                        include module name in representation of classes\r\n                        (default: None)\r\n  --only-classnames, -k\r\n                        don't show attributes and methods in the class boxes;\r\n                        this disables -f values (default: False)\r\n  --output <format>, -o <format>\r\n                        create a *.<format> output file if format is\r\n                        available. Available formats are: dot, vcg, puml,\r\n                        plantuml, mmd, html. Any other format will be tried to\r\n                        create by means of the 'dot' command line tool, which\r\n                        requires a graphviz installation. (default: dot)\r\n  --colorized           Use colored output. Classes/modules of the same\r\n                        package get the same color. (default: False)\r\n  --max-color-depth <depth>\r\n                        Use separate colors up to package depth of <depth>\r\n                        (default: 2)\r\n  --color-palette <color1,color2,...>\r\n                        Comma separated list of colors to use (default:\r\n                        ('aliceblue', 'antiquewhite', 'aquamarine',\r\n                        'burlywood', 'cadetblue', 'chartreuse', 'chocolate',\r\n                        'coral', 'cornflowerblue', 'cyan', 'darkgoldenrod',\r\n                        'darkseagreen', 'dodgerblue', 'forestgreen', 'gold',\r\n                        'hotpink', 'mediumspringgreen'))\r\n  --ignore <file[,file...]>\r\n                        Files or directories to be skipped. They should be\r\n                        base names, not paths. (default: ('CVS',))\r\n  --project <project name>, -p <project name>\r\n                        set the project name. (default: )\r\n  --output-directory <output_directory>, -d <output_directory>\r\n                        set the output directory path. (default: )\r\n  --source-roots <path>[,<path>...]\r\n                        Add paths to the list of the source roots. Supports\r\n                        globbing patterns. The source root is an absolute path\r\n                        or a path relative to the current working directory\r\n                        used to determine a package namespace for modules\r\n                        located under the source root. (default: ())","cwd":"C:\\Users\\west2\\.openclaw\\workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1771153249314}}
